-- Connecticut Water Completes Purchase of Maine Utility to Expand
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2012-12-11T12:08:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-11/connecticut-water-completes-purchase-of-maine-utility-to-expand.html
Connecticut Water Service Inc. (CTWS) 
closed on its $19.8 million acquisition of Biddeford and Saco
Water Co. in  Maine  to raise to almost 400,000 people that the
utility provides water to in the U.S. Northeast.  The Clinton, Connecticut-based company is now one of the 10
largest publicly traded water utilities in the U.S., it said in
a statement. The shares have risen 16 percent this year compared
with a 25 percent gain by the 7-member Bloomberg Americas Water
Index.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Hackley in London at 
